Comment: Predicative Construction with a Same Participant Clausal Argument  Clauses 1:38  John is able to read a book.-*-  For 'able to see things', delete the 'things'.  Gen. 27:1 Isaac was not able to see well.  The word 'thing' can't be modified by either an adjective or a relative clause.  Luke 6:42 You will be able to see other things well.  But this causes a problem in Ephesians 5:13 When something is in darkness, people are not able to see IT.  But when light shines on something, people are able to see IT.   I've turned this structure off, and I'll mark the NPs as Implicit Info.-*-  Daniel 5:23 Those gods are not able to hear.  The noun must not be modified by a relative clause as in Luke 8:10 ... able to hear the things that I say ...  I've turned this structure off because I'm marking those NPs as Implicit.-*-
